symmetry comes from the $g_T D_1$ term, while the $g_T^\\perp D_1$\nterm gives the main contribution to the $\\cos(2\\phi_h -\\phi_S)$ asymmetry; the\nother two $T$-odd terms almost give negligible contributions. In particular,\nthe $\\cos(2\\phi_h -\\phi_S)$ asymmetry provides a unique opportunity to probe\nthe distribution $g_T^\\perp$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Dec 2014 14:55:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Feb 2015 03:42:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-05"}
